# drift-kit KPI registry — one plugin name per line, # comments (the gates.list
# grammar). Names resolve against DRIFT_KIT_KPI_DIRS first (default: your gates
# dir), then each vendored kit's kpis/. Drop a same-named file in your gates dir
# to shadow a bundled KPI; delete a line to opt out. Copy this file to your
# gates dir as kpis.list and prune to the surfaces you actually run.

# Lead — weighted high; act before drift compounds.
kpi-task-split
kpi-gate-backlog
kpi-amendment-age
kpi-deferred-age
kpi-prompt-friction
kpi-always-loaded
kpi-settings-local
kpi-gate-runtime
kpi-overhead
kpi-price-table-age

# Lag — weighted low; undercounts by construction. kpi-knowledge-friction reads
# drift-kit's knowledge-friction loop (its capture convention + close triage); it
# shows n/a until the log exists. A consumer with a structured lag source adds its own.
kpi-knowledge-friction
